4.46/5  rDev 0%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5I feel like a broken record at times, but this is another outstanding beer by TG.
Unlike the Pompeii or the Sol Hunter, this beer finishes with a crispness & bite, unique for an IBU of around 60. Pours an orangeish amber color with a stark white head with a big tropical nose with hints of grass & pine...it's a bit spicier than the nose on a lot of TG brews. The flavor profile follows the nose nicely, with juicy tangerine notes & a piney bite. Finishes strong and lingers pleasantly. A smoother mouthfeel than I imagined throughout the taste, but not quite a velvety smooth finish like Sue.
Overall, another excellent beer in the stable and one I'd place ahead of Sosus & Light Speed, but behind Twisted Galaxy and the obvious. If you can find it, grab it. It won't disappoint. 782 charactersumichfan, Feb 28, 2017
