4.26/5  rDev -4.5%look: 3 | smell: 3.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5A big thanks to Jeff for this. I'm a huge fan of this series. 22oz. bomber into a Surly teku. Shared with schen9303. 
Pours New England-y if that makes any sense. Cloudy and frothy. Nose is pineapple, starfruit and citrus. The flavors are there but its pretty mellow. Beer opens pine, citrus, starfruit and grapefruit. There's a nice juiciness in this but its expertly balanced by a citrus rind hop bitterness. A light grassy bitterness at the end with a mellow, tropical fruit sweetness to finish. Very nice. Body is light to medium with moderate to low carbonation. Smooth on the palate and dry and quenching going down. Very drinkable. 
Excellent as usual. Its amazing that a beer this flavorful is delivered as a pale ale. 728 charactersSpeedwayJim, Feb 01, 2017
