4.05/5  rDev -9.2%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 422 oz. bottle dated 3/8/16 split with my wife. 
Pour is light orange & very active. Very nice tropical scent on this baby, with the sharp, tangy twist of pineapple ascendant. Zesty & nice. 
Xhops - Gold harks to the lovely tradition of Pompeii & Sue more than the sadness that has been some of the previous Xhops ventures. The tropical fiesta continues through the taste: mango, pineapple, citrus, those weird little genetically engineered Halo things (they are oranges, right?). Electric bitterness backs up the fruit, mild earthiness, light sweetness. Very dry & nicely drinkable. 
I find most ‘tropical’ IPAs to bear too much fruit & too little IPA sting - this one brings both in spades. I could lush out on this. Excellent beer. 740 charactersmaximum12, Apr 17, 2016
