4.59/5  rDev +2.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.5BOD 3/6/16.  Pours an almost clear pale amber with a touch of haze.  World class head volume, lacing and retention.
Rich very aromatic world class nose of citrus, with a good dose of tropical citrus. Orange and pineapple are the strongest components with light zest, mango and a touch of spruce underneath.  As it warms, an earthy dank note develops.
Light full body that is quite smooth and finishes a bit creamy.  Perfectly balanced world class carbonation level with a strong effervescent middle and a rollicking finely bubbled prickly finish.
The flavor profile is world class.  It is hop flavor centered and has pitch perfect balance.  While quite complex, excellent flavor separation occurs.  The sharper flavors arrive first (zest, orange) than mellow into pineapple and mango in the middle.  The middle brings a very low level of bitterness that is rind based, but has a light spruce note as well.  A slightly grainy biscuit sweetness occurs mid-palate allowing the sweet tropicals to shine.  As the finish approaches, a significant dank wave coats the tongue.  The finish is a slow tasty dank fade of light tropical sweetness, zest and spruce.  This lives up to the hype. 1,183 characterstillmac62, Apr 01, 2016
