4.29/5  rDev -3.8%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25I've been looking forward to this beer ever since i missed out on the first batch. I sat the bottle to warm to slightly colder than cellar temp. 
Look: pours a translucent gold color, white head and some carbonation bubbles coming up. I was surprised this wasn't as hazy as some TG beers, and slightly disappointed. 
Smell: big time fruits. Nectarines, peaches, and a slight passion fruit scent. 
Taste: follows the nose to an extent, with a little more malt, slight slight pine and almost a alcohol taste. 
Feel: medium mouthfeel and a bit more bitterness than I expect from Toppling. I was hoping for a softer mouthfeel and juicy, less bitter feel. 
Overall: By all means, this is an excellent beer and one that should be sought after; however, Toppling Goliath has high expectations based on prior beers and name. I would buy more, but it slightly missed expectations. 875 charactersCfred371, Mar 25, 2016
