4.52/5  rDev +1.3%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.75Poured from a 22 oz. bottle into a chalice.
Appearance: Pours a very hazy golden orange with a moderate amount of bubbles. Slight finger of white head that settles into a thin patchy layer. 
Smell: A very juicy and tropical hop forward aroma with a scent of citrus fruit and grass. Big upfront presence of citrus hops with a scent of mango, grapefruit, orange peel, melon, pineapple, tangerine, lemon, and peach. Also some earthy hop hints of grass. Subtle malt hints of caramel, grains, and yeast. A pretty good juicy aroma. 
Taste: Like it smells, a very tropical and juicy hop dominated taste with big notes of citrus fruit and grass. Big juicy taste of citrus hops with notes of grapefruit, mango, melon, orange peel, tangerine, pineapple, peach, and lemon. Good notes of grassy hops and pine. Light background malt notes of caramel, grains, and yeast. A very good taste. 
Mouthfeel: Medium bodied with a moderate amount of carbonation. Very juicy and fairly oily with a drying finish. 
Overall: Another really good hop bomb from Toppling Goliath. Big juicy taste of tropical fruit with a moderate body and bitterness. Really tasty. 1,141 charactersMattyG85, Dec 30, 2015
