4.5/5  rDev +0.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5650ml bottle. Served in a TG snifter glass.
Pours a hazy and cloudy light copper body, like a light-bodied cider. One finger white head, fair retention, rings of lacing and a thin collar. Looks even hazier than normal. Smells of citrus, orange rind, melon, passion fruit, minimal grainy pale malt, a bit of minerality, perhaps a little pine sap. It's really quite exquisite in terms of how complex, juicy and dry the aroma is, without punching you in the face over and over again with citrus. Flavour is similarly great. It's not extreme and in your face, but the juicy citrus, honey dew, tangerines and passion fruit dominate the palate with a minimal caramel and grainy sweetness. A bit of orange rind bitterness rounds things out, particularly on the backend. Mouthfeel is medium bodied, good carbonation, finish is a combination of orange rind and grainy/mineral finish that is typical of Toppling Goliath. Overall, this was an excellent APA where the hops are done quite well, covering the entire aroma and palate with something interesting and delicious from Point A all the way to Point Z, sparing nothing. This is would be a really nice one to put in a rotating 4-pack. Well done, TG. 1,193 charactersStevedore, Dec 29, 2015
